#### The Shorter Poems

### Chaucers Wordes unto Adam, His Owne Scriveyn

<span id="an_1"></span> Adam scriveyn, if ever it thee bifalle  
<span id="an_2"></span> Boece or Troylus for to wryten newe,  
<span id="an_3"></span> Under thy long lokkes thou most have the
scalle,  
<span id="an_4"></span> But after my makyng thow wryte more trewe;  
<span id="an_5"></span> So ofte adaye I mot thy werk renewe,  
<span id="an_6"></span> It to correcte and eke to rubbe and scrape,  
<span id="an_7"></span> And al is thorugh thy negligence and rape.  

